<subSubSection lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="105" pageId="5" pageNumber="104" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,1482,2025]" pageId="5" pageNumber="104">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,289,1518,1543]" pageId="5" pageNumber="104">Description</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[307,367,1518,1543]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="104">Head</emphasis>
. Antennae shortly bipectinate, filiform at apex in male, filiform in female. Frons flattened, width similar to diameter of compound eyes. Labial palpus short, just extending beyond frons. Proboscis well developed. Chaetosemata small, with a few long setae. Vertex rough-scaled.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,1482,2025]" pageId="5" pageNumber="104">
<emphasis box="[199,287,1626,1651]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="104">Thorax.</emphasis>
Foreleg with well-developed epiphysis; tibial spurs absent. Midleg with one pair of terminal tibial spurs. Hind tibia with two pairs of spurs in both sexes, dilated in male with hair-pencil and a short terminal extension.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,1482,2025]" pageId="5" pageNumber="104">
<emphasis box="[199,328,1734,1759]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="104">Wing shape</emphasis>
. Apex of forewing blunt, that of hind wing rounded; outer margin of forewing slightly curved, that of hind wing forming a distinct protrusion at end of M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[759,767,1785,1799]" fontSize="6" pageId="5" pageNumber="104">3</subScript>
(
<figureCitation box="[778,879,1770,1795]" captionStart="FIGURES 4–10" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1869,1892]" captionTargetBox="[215,1416,345,1838]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,337,1849]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 4–10. FIGURES 4–5. Neochloroglyphica perbella gen. nov., sp. nov. 4, male, holotype, ZFMK; 5, female, paratype, IZCAS; 1.5x life size. FIGURE 6. Gongziding, Deqin, Yunnan, one type-locality of Neochloroglyphica perbella. FIGURES 7–10. Male genitalia of the Neohipparchini species. 7, Neochloroglyphica perbella, paratype; 8, Chloroglyphica variegata (Butler); 9, Neohipparchus vallata (Butler); 10, Chlororithra fea Butler. Scale bars = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2606024/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="104">Figs 4, 5</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,1482,2025]" pageId="5" pageNumber="104">
<emphasis box="[199,297,1811,1834]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="104">Venation</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[312,380,1809,1834]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1613,1635]" captionText="FIGURE 3. Venation of Neochloroglyphica perbella sp. nov." pageId="5" pageNumber="104">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
): Frenulum developed. Forewing: R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[787,795,1824,1838]" fontSize="6" pageId="5" pageNumber="104">1</subScript>
free; R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[878,899,1824,1838]" fontSize="6" pageId="5" pageNumber="104">2-5</subScript>
arising before upper angle of cell; M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1314,1322,1824,1838]" fontSize="6" pageId="5" pageNumber="104">1</subScript>
free; base of M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[208,216,1863,1877]" fontSize="6" pageId="5" pageNumber="104">2</subScript>
close to M 
<subScript attach="right" box="[348,356,1863,1877]" fontSize="6" pageId="5" pageNumber="104">1</subScript>
, M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[396,404,1863,1877]" fontSize="6" pageId="5" pageNumber="104">3</subScript>
and CuA 
<subScript attach="left" box="[516,524,1863,1877]" fontSize="6" pageId="5" pageNumber="104">1</subScript>
separate; discocellulars deeply incurved between veins M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1191,1199,1863,1877]" fontSize="6" pageId="5" pageNumber="104">2</subScript>
and M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1283,1291,1863,1877]" fontSize="6" pageId="5" pageNumber="104">3</subScript>
. Hind wing: Sc+R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[213,221,1902,1916]" fontSize="6" pageId="5" pageNumber="104">1</subScript>
close to upper vein of cell at one point near base; Rs and M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[932,940,1902,1916]" fontSize="6" pageId="5" pageNumber="104">1</subScript>
free, M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1035,1043,1902,1916]" fontSize="6" pageId="5" pageNumber="104">3</subScript>
and CuA 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1155,1163,1902,1916]" fontSize="6" pageId="5" pageNumber="104">1</subScript>
separate; discocellulars deeply incurved between veins M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[529,537,1941,1955]" fontSize="6" pageId="5" pageNumber="104">2</subScript>
and M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[616,624,1941,1955]" fontSize="6" pageId="5" pageNumber="104">3</subScript>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,1482,2025]" lastBlockId="6.[151,1436,151,320]" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="105" pageId="5" pageNumber="104">
<emphasis box="[199,365,1964,1989]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="104">Male genitalia</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[381,455,1964,1989]" captionStart="FIGURES 4–10" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1869,1892]" captionTargetBox="[215,1416,345,1838]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,337,1849]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 4–10. FIGURES 4–5. Neochloroglyphica perbella gen. nov., sp. nov. 4, male, holotype, ZFMK; 5, female, paratype, IZCAS; 1.5x life size. FIGURE 6. Gongziding, Deqin, Yunnan, one type-locality of Neochloroglyphica perbella. FIGURES 7–10. Male genitalia of the Neohipparchini species. 7, Neochloroglyphica perbella, paratype; 8, Chloroglyphica variegata (Butler); 9, Neohipparchus vallata (Butler); 10, Chlororithra fea Butler. Scale bars = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2606024/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="104">Figs 7</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[469,500,1965,1989]" captionStart="FIGURES 11–17" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1148,1171]" captionTargetBox="[177,1412,237,1093]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[151,1436,193,1127]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 11–17. Male genitalia, aedeagus and the eighth segment of the Neohipparchini species. 11, Chloroglyphica glaucochrista glaucochrista (Prout); 12, Neochloroglyphica perbella, paratype; 13, Chloroglyphica glaucochrista glaucochrista (Prout), 14, Neohipparchus vallata (Butler); 15, Neochloroglyphica perbella, paratype; 16, Chloroglyphica glaucochrista glaucochrista (Prout); 17, Chlororithra fea Butler. Scale bars =1mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2606028/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="104">12</figureCitation>
). Uncus shortly digitiform, blunt terminally. Socii very long, expanded inwards at middle, narrow at base and tapering posteriorly. Gnathos with lateral arms longer than socii, medial process long, slender and pointed. Valva with middle part expanded, tip pointed with a tiny tooth; costal base with a stout hooked process, tip spinose; subventral margin strongly sclerotized at middle, appearing as a sclerotized ridge, with three or four tiny teeth posteriorly. Transtilla as a pair of slightly sclerotized processes. Juxta as a rounded sclerite, not developed. Saccus small, protruding. Coremata present, very weak. Aedeagus slender, posterior half sclerotized laterally, with a pointed tooth at tip.
</paragraph>
<caption box="[151,775,1613,1635]" pageId="6" pageNumber="105">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,775,1613,1635]" box="[151,775,1613,1635]" pageId="6" pageNumber="105">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,1613,1635]" pageId="6" pageNumber="105">FIGURE 3.</emphasis>
Venation of 
<taxonomicName authority="Han &amp; Skou &amp; Cheng, 2019" authorityName="Han &amp; Skou &amp; Cheng" authorityYear="2019" box="[404,689,1613,1635]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Neochloroglyphica" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="105" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="perbella" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[404,689,1613,1635]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="105">Neochloroglyphica perbella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[695,775,1613,1634]" pageId="6" pageNumber="105" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,1674,2023]" pageId="6" pageNumber="105">
<emphasis box="[199,394,1674,1699]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="105">Female genitalia</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[414,502,1674,1699]" captionStart="FIGURES 18–26" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1887,1910]" captionTargetBox="[164,1414,595,1820]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,591,1866]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 18–26. Female genitalia of the Neohipparchini species. 18, Neochloroglyphica perbella, paratype, scale bar = 1mm; 19, Chloroglyphica variegata (Butler); 20, Chloroglyphica glaucochrista glaucochrista (Prout); 21, Neohipparchus vallata (Butler); 22, Neohipparchus hypoleuca (Hampson), 23, Chlororithra fea Butler, 24, Mixochlora vittata (Moore), 25. Loxochila kina (Swinhoe), 26. Geometra glaucaria Ménétriés." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2606032/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="105">Fig. 18</figureCitation>
). Ovipositor lobes sclerotized and smooth, not papillate. Apophyses posteriores about five times the length of apophyses anteriores. Lamella postvaginalis an irregular sclerotized region. Antrum developed. Ductus bursae short, wrinkled, broadened at middle. Corpus bursae large, rounded; signum a tiny process.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,1192,1818,1843]" pageId="6" pageNumber="105" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,1674,2023]" box="[199,1192,1818,1843]" pageId="6" pageNumber="105">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,326,1818,1843]" pageId="6" pageNumber="105">Etymology</emphasis>
. The generic name references the close relation to the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Warren. In" authorityYear="1894" box="[1010,1185,1818,1843]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Chloroglyphica" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="105" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1010,1185,1818,1843]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="105">Chloroglyphica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="107" pageId="6" pageNumber="105" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,1674,2023]" lastBlockId="8.[151,1436,1307,1727]" lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="107" pageId="6" pageNumber="105">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,314,1854,1879]" pageId="6" pageNumber="105">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. On the wing pattern, 
<taxonomicName authority="Han &amp; Skou &amp; Cheng, 2019" authorityName="Han &amp; Skou &amp; Cheng" authorityYear="2019" box="[579,793,1854,1879]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Neochloroglyphica" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="100" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[579,793,1854,1879]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="105">Neochloroglyphica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is most similar to the genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Inoue. The" authorityName="Inoue. The" authorityYear="1944" box="[1132,1436,1854,1879]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Neohipparchus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="105" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1132,1302,1854,1879]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="105">Neohipparchus</emphasis>
Inoue. The
</taxonomicName>
transverse lines are much slenderer than in most species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Inoue. The" authorityYear="1944" box="[890,1060,1890,1915]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Neohipparchus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="105" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[890,1060,1890,1915]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="105">Neohipparchus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(such as 
<taxonomicName authority="Butler" authorityName="Butler" authorityYear="1878" box="[1187,1392,1890,1915]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Neohipparchus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="105" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vallata">
<emphasis box="[1187,1305,1890,1915]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="105">N. vallata</emphasis>
Butler
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Oberthur" authorityName="Oberthur" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Neohipparchus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="105" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vervactoraria">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="105">N. vervactoraria</emphasis>
Oberthür
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Oberthur" authorityName="Oberthur" box="[425,758,1926,1951]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Neohipparchus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="105" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="verjucodumnaria">
<emphasis box="[425,650,1926,1951]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="105">N. verjucodumnaria</emphasis>
Oberthür
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Warren" authorityName="Warren" authorityYear="1897" box="[811,1040,1926,1951]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Neohipparchus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="105" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="maculata">
<emphasis box="[811,949,1926,1951]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="105">N. maculata</emphasis>
Warren
</taxonomicName>
), and lack the brown shading of the antemedial and postmedial lines. Compared to the 
<typeStatus box="[721,769,1963,1987]" pageId="6" pageNumber="105">type</typeStatus>
species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Inoue. The" authorityYear="1944" box="[895,1065,1962,1987]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Neohipparchus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="105" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[895,1065,1962,1987]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="105">Neohipparchus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Butler" authorityName="Butler" authorityYear="1878" box="[1080,1270,1962,1987]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Neohipparchus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="105" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vallata">
<emphasis box="[1080,1191,1962,1987]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="105">N. vallata</emphasis>
Butler
</taxonomicName>
, the hind wing fringes of 
<taxonomicName authority="Han &amp; Skou &amp; Cheng, 2019" authorityName="Han &amp; Skou &amp; Cheng" authorityYear="2019" box="[284,498,1998,2023]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Neochloroglyphica" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="100" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[284,498,1998,2023]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="105">Neochloroglyphica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
only bear one brown tuft, whereas 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Butler" authorityYear="1878" box="[959,1037,1998,2023]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Neohipparchus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="105" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vallata">
<emphasis box="[959,1037,1998,2023]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="105">vallata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has two. In the male genitalia, 
<taxonomicName authority="Han &amp; Skou &amp; Cheng, 2019" authorityName="Han &amp; Skou &amp; Cheng" authorityYear="2019" box="[151,365,151,176]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Neochloroglyphica" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="100" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[151,365,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="106">Neochloroglyphica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is characterized within the 
<taxonomicName box="[685,859,151,176]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="106" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Neohipparchini">Neohipparchini</taxonomicName>
by the presence of a small spine on the tip of the valva. 
<taxonomicName authority="Han &amp; Skou &amp; Cheng, 2019" authorityName="Han &amp; Skou &amp; Cheng" authorityYear="2019" box="[227,441,188,213]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Neochloroglyphica" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="100" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[227,441,188,213]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="106">Neochloroglyphica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a small uncus, developed socii, and comparatively simple valvae. Compared to the 
<typeStatus box="[151,199,224,248]" pageId="7" pageNumber="106">type</typeStatus>
species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Inoue. The" authorityYear="1944" box="[324,494,223,248]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Neohipparchus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="106" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[324,494,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="106">Neohipparchus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[510,578,223,248]" captionStart="FIGURES 4–10" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1869,1892]" captionTargetBox="[215,1416,345,1838]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,337,1849]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 4–10. FIGURES 4–5. Neochloroglyphica perbella gen. nov., sp. nov. 4, male, holotype, ZFMK; 5, female, paratype, IZCAS; 1.5x life size. FIGURE 6. Gongziding, Deqin, Yunnan, one type-locality of Neochloroglyphica perbella. FIGURES 7–10. Male genitalia of the Neohipparchini species. 7, Neochloroglyphica perbella, paratype; 8, Chloroglyphica variegata (Butler); 9, Neohipparchus vallata (Butler); 10, Chlororithra fea Butler. Scale bars = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2606024/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="106">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
), the uncus of 
<taxonomicName authority="Han &amp; Skou &amp; Cheng, 2019" authorityName="Han &amp; Skou &amp; Cheng" authorityYear="2019" box="[743,957,223,248]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Neochloroglyphica" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="100" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[743,957,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="106">Neochloroglyphica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is quite small, but it is as large as the socii in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Butler" authorityYear="1878" box="[180,290,260,285]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Neohipparchus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="106" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vallata">
<emphasis box="[180,290,260,285]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="106">N. vallata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; the costa lacks a spinose cluster but bears a hooked process; the ventral margin of the valva bears a sclerotized ridge and spines, which are lacking in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Butler" authorityYear="1878" box="[715,827,1307,1332]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Neohipparchus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="107" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vallata">
<emphasis box="[715,827,1307,1332]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="107">N. vallata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; the lateral arms of the gnathos of 
<taxonomicName authority="Han &amp; Skou &amp; Cheng, 2019" authorityName="Han &amp; Skou &amp; Cheng" authorityYear="2019" box="[1222,1436,1307,1332]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Neochloroglyphica" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="100" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1222,1436,1307,1332]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="107">Neochloroglyphica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are much longer than those of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Butler" authorityYear="1878" box="[524,640,1343,1368]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Neohipparchus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="107" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vallata">
<emphasis box="[524,640,1343,1368]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="107">N. vallata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; the male eighth tergite has two small hooked lateral processes in 
<taxonomicName authority="Han &amp; Skou &amp; Cheng, 2019" authorityName="Han &amp; Skou &amp; Cheng" authorityYear="2019" box="[151,364,1379,1404]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Neochloroglyphica" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="100" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[151,364,1379,1404]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="107">Neochloroglyphica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, while 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Butler" authorityYear="1878" box="[447,557,1379,1404]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Neohipparchus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="107" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vallata">
<emphasis box="[447,557,1379,1404]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="107">N. vallata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has three developed processes; sternite 
<quantity box="[1005,1047,1379,1404]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.032" pageId="8" pageNumber="107" unit="in" value="8.0">8 in</quantity>
the male is deeply concave and Vshaped in 
<taxonomicName authority="Han &amp; Skou &amp; Cheng, 2019" authorityName="Han &amp; Skou &amp; Cheng" authorityYear="2019" box="[272,486,1415,1440]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Neochloroglyphica" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="100" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[272,486,1415,1440]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="107">Neochloroglyphica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but unmodified in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Butler" authorityYear="1878" box="[722,837,1415,1440]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Neohipparchus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="107" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vallata">
<emphasis box="[722,837,1415,1440]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="107">N. vallata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName authority="Han &amp; Skou &amp; Cheng, 2019" authorityName="Han &amp; Skou &amp; Cheng" authorityYear="2019" box="[854,1068,1415,1440]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Neochloroglyphica" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="100" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[854,1068,1415,1440]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="107">Neochloroglyphica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
also can be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName authority="(Butler)" authorityName="Butler" baseAuthorityName="Butler" box="[151,540,1451,1476]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Chloroglyphica" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="107" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="variegata">
<emphasis box="[151,442,1451,1476]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="107">Chloroglyphica variegata</emphasis>
(Butler)
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[557,626,1451,1476]" captionStart="FIGURES 4–10" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1869,1892]" captionTargetBox="[215,1416,345,1838]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,337,1849]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 4–10. FIGURES 4–5. Neochloroglyphica perbella gen. nov., sp. nov. 4, male, holotype, ZFMK; 5, female, paratype, IZCAS; 1.5x life size. FIGURE 6. Gongziding, Deqin, Yunnan, one type-locality of Neochloroglyphica perbella. FIGURES 7–10. Male genitalia of the Neohipparchini species. 7, Neochloroglyphica perbella, paratype; 8, Chloroglyphica variegata (Butler); 9, Neohipparchus vallata (Butler); 10, Chlororithra fea Butler. Scale bars = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2606024/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="107">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
) and 
<taxonomicName authority="Butler" authorityName="Butler" authorityYear="1889" box="[693,916,1451,1476]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Chlororithra" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="107" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[693,837,1451,1476]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="107">Chlororithra</emphasis>
Butler
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[933,1017,1451,1476]" captionStart="FIGURES 4–10" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1869,1892]" captionTargetBox="[215,1416,345,1838]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,337,1849]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 4–10. FIGURES 4–5. Neochloroglyphica perbella gen. nov., sp. nov. 4, male, holotype, ZFMK; 5, female, paratype, IZCAS; 1.5x life size. FIGURE 6. Gongziding, Deqin, Yunnan, one type-locality of Neochloroglyphica perbella. FIGURES 7–10. Male genitalia of the Neohipparchini species. 7, Neochloroglyphica perbella, paratype; 8, Chloroglyphica variegata (Butler); 9, Neohipparchus vallata (Butler); 10, Chlororithra fea Butler. Scale bars = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2606024/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="107">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
) by the small uncus, different costal base and ventral margin. 
<taxonomicName authority="Han &amp; Skou &amp; Cheng, 2019" authorityName="Han &amp; Skou &amp; Cheng" authorityYear="2019" box="[435,649,1487,1512]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Neochloroglyphica" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="100" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[435,649,1487,1512]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="107">Neochloroglyphica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
shares a modified eighth segment with 
<taxonomicName authority="Prout" authorityName="Prout" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Chloroglyphica" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="107" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="glaucochrista">
<emphasis box="[1100,1436,1487,1512]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="107">Chloroglyphica glaucochrista</emphasis>
Prout
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Butler" authorityYear="1889" box="[275,419,1523,1548]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Chlororithra" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="107" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[275,419,1523,1548]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="107">Chlororithra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but can be differentiated by the following differences: the eighth tergite is shallowly curved in the very broad middle part and bears two lateral processes in 
<taxonomicName authority="Han &amp; Skou &amp; Cheng, 2019" authorityName="Han &amp; Skou &amp; Cheng" authorityYear="2019" box="[1002,1216,1559,1584]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Neochloroglyphica" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="100" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1002,1216,1559,1584]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="107">Neochloroglyphica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[1235,1322,1559,1584]" captionStart="FIGURES 11–17" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1148,1171]" captionTargetBox="[177,1412,237,1093]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[151,1436,193,1127]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 11–17. Male genitalia, aedeagus and the eighth segment of the Neohipparchini species. 11, Chloroglyphica glaucochrista glaucochrista (Prout); 12, Neochloroglyphica perbella, paratype; 13, Chloroglyphica glaucochrista glaucochrista (Prout), 14, Neohipparchus vallata (Butler); 15, Neochloroglyphica perbella, paratype; 16, Chloroglyphica glaucochrista glaucochrista (Prout); 17, Chlororithra fea Butler. Scale bars =1mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2606028/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="107">Fig. 15</figureCitation>
), but two triangular processes are present in 
<taxonomicName box="[537,872,1595,1620]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Chloroglyphica" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="107" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="glaucochrista">
<emphasis box="[537,872,1595,1620]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="107">Chloroglyphica glaucochrista</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[887,968,1595,1620]" captionStart="FIGURES 11–17" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1148,1171]" captionTargetBox="[177,1412,237,1093]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[151,1436,193,1127]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 11–17. Male genitalia, aedeagus and the eighth segment of the Neohipparchini species. 11, Chloroglyphica glaucochrista glaucochrista (Prout); 12, Neochloroglyphica perbella, paratype; 13, Chloroglyphica glaucochrista glaucochrista (Prout), 14, Neohipparchus vallata (Butler); 15, Neochloroglyphica perbella, paratype; 16, Chloroglyphica glaucochrista glaucochrista (Prout); 17, Chlororithra fea Butler. Scale bars =1mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2606028/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="107">Fig. 16</figureCitation>
) and are curved in a semicircular curve in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Butler. Scale" authorityYear="1889" box="[151,340,1631,1656]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Chlororithra" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="107" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fea">
<emphasis box="[151,340,1631,1656]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="107">Chlororithra fea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[360,449,1631,1656]" captionStart="FIGURES 11–17" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1148,1171]" captionTargetBox="[177,1412,237,1093]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[151,1436,193,1127]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 11–17. Male genitalia, aedeagus and the eighth segment of the Neohipparchini species. 11, Chloroglyphica glaucochrista glaucochrista (Prout); 12, Neochloroglyphica perbella, paratype; 13, Chloroglyphica glaucochrista glaucochrista (Prout), 14, Neohipparchus vallata (Butler); 15, Neochloroglyphica perbella, paratype; 16, Chloroglyphica glaucochrista glaucochrista (Prout); 17, Chlororithra fea Butler. Scale bars =1mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2606028/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="107">Fig. 17</figureCitation>
); the eighth sternite of 
<taxonomicName authority="Han &amp; Skou &amp; Cheng, 2019" authorityName="Han &amp; Skou &amp; Cheng" authorityYear="2019" box="[731,945,1631,1656]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Neochloroglyphica" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="100" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[731,945,1631,1656]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="107">Neochloroglyphica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is less developed than in 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Chloroglyphica" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="107" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="glaucochrista">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="107">Chloroglyphica glaucochrista</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. In the female genitalia, 
<taxonomicName authority="Han &amp; Skou &amp; Cheng, 2019" authorityName="Han &amp; Skou &amp; Cheng" authorityYear="2019" box="[594,808,1667,1692]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Neochloroglyphica" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="100" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[594,808,1667,1692]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="107">Neochloroglyphica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be differentiated by the presence of the developed antrum.
</paragraph>
